AIM:
To model a microneedle using COMSOL and analyze its structural behavior under applied load.
SOFTWARE REQUIRED:
COMSOL Multiphysics
PROCEDURE:
Model Wizard:
    Select 3D
    Select Physics → Solid Mechanics
    Click Add
    Select Study → Stationary
    Click Done
GEOMETRY 1
    Set Length unit = µm
CONE (MICRONEEDLE TIP)
    Right-click Geometry → Cone
    Height = 600 µm
    Base radius = 150 µm
    Top radius = 5 µm
    Click Build All
CYLINDER (BASE SUPPORT)
    Right-click Geometry → Cylinder
    Height = 200 µm
    Radius = 150 µm
    Position below the cone
    Click Build All
MATERIALS
    Add Material → Built-in → Silicon
    Apply to geometry
SOLID MECHANICS
  FIXED CONSTRAINT
    Select bottom face of cylinder → Fixed
  BOUNDARY LOAD
    Select tip of microneedle
    Apply force = 0.001 N (example)
MESH
    Right-click Mesh → Free Tetrahedral
    Click Build Mesh
STUDY
    Click Compute

RESULT:
    The stress and displacement distribution of the microneedle under applied load are successfully obtained.
